==English==
===Etymology===
Contraction of ''[[w:Æthelthryth|St. Audrey's]] [[lace]]'', with reference to Saint Audrey or Æthelthryth (d. 679), an Anglo-Saxon saint in whose honour a fair was held.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈtɔ:dri leɪs/}}

===Noun phrase===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{obsolete}} A [[silk]] ribbon or string worn as a necklace in the 16th and early-17th centuries.

